line_1: Then strait ev'n wit itself shall raise dislike;
line_2: A voice perhaps our ear shall harshly strike,

line_1: Just hint a fault, and hesitate dislike;
line_2: Willing to wound, and yet afraid to strike,
And stretch'd his Paw to strike.

line_1: Contempt and scorn might look dislike,
line_2: Did not the tender nonsense strike,

line_1: Faction's below him, if he does dislike,
line_2: He always dares to show his Face, and strike;

line_1: To female rules profess'd a brave dislike,
line_2: Her majesty could swear as well as strike.
